m. India's embrace of globalization has created employment opportunities for Northeast migrants in many capitalistic enterprises: shopping malls, restaurants, and call centers. They have been able to create their own "map" of Delhi and their own communities within the larger and often unfriendly one of the metropolis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAnthropology. 0aMigration, InternalzIndiazDelhi. 0aRural-urban migrationzIndiazDelhi. 0aSociology, UrbanzIndiazDelhi. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106627880 cprintz978908964422040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048516230?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048516230zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048516230/original  a978-3-11-060651-5 AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8 Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1 AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA